‘Highly reputable FMCG business seeking HR Operations Manager based in Riyadh’
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/04/30 08:01:19
Ref. JB3045736
Job Description
With fantastic brand names and a truly entrepreneurial and ethical culture lead by a strong management team, it’s no wonder this leading FMCG business continues to expand across the market.
To further support this an experienced HR Operations Manager is required to ensure that the HR services and capabilities are exceptional.
The role has responsibility for a team of 20 in areas covering HR systems, process improvement, performance management and payroll.
You will support the Director in developing and implementing HR functional processes, technology systems and transformation projects.
Budgeting and manpower costing is a key element of this role as is managing the performance management system policies and procedures across the various divisions.
You will communicate regularly the various business and department Heads in the divisions and closely with the HR Operations Director.
Skills
This role requires a solid HR professional with at LEAST 9 years HR experience and 5 at a manager level.
Additionally you MUST have the following to be seriously considered for this role:
Be an Arabic speaker
Strong computer skills
Have knowledge of business processes, reengineering/mapping
Have worked in an large organization with more than 500 employees
Gained overall HR operations experience
Managed teams
Exposure to payroll
Education
degree
